channel.title: First Model
channel.description:
I used a dragon scimitar base and I tried to edit enough so that you wouldn't really be able to tell that I used the dragon scimitar as the base, but I know that you can still tell that it was made from a dragon scimitar. Any tips on how to make it better would be appreciated. Used this to get to learn the basic interface of Metasequoia, probably gonna start making from scratch from now on. I don't have ints or anything for it, I just edited it a little bit.
Front: [IMG]http://i349.photobucket.com/albums/q398/sk4r3dpkz/BlueSwordModelFront.jpg[/img]
Top: [IMG]http://i349.photobucket.com/albums/q398/sk4r3dpkz/BlueSwordModelTop.jpg[/img]
Right: [IMG]http://i349.photobucket.com/albums/q398/sk4r3dpkz/BlueSwordModelRight.jpg[/img]
Left: [IMG]http://i349.photobucket.com/albums/q398/sk4r3dpkz/BlueSwordModelLeft.jpg[/img]
Credits: 2% To Me 98% To Jagex
Once again, any tips on how to make it better would be appreciated. Also please note, this is my first time making (I actually should say editing) a model, and my first time using Metasequoia, so I am sorry if it doesn't live up to the standards this community is probably looking for. Again, I will most likely start making them from scratch from now on. Thank You!
